[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "A Beerothite.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Beeroth was one of the four cities of the Gibeonites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 9:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and was allotted with the others to the tribe of Benjamin (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 18:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It is identified with the modern ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "El-Bireh, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nine miles north of Jerusalem. It is mentioned here, in the past tense, that Beeroth “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "reckoned to Benjamin,” because in the time of the writer it was no longer inhabited. The fact that the murderers of Ish-bosheth were of his own tribe is made prominent.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Samuel 4:2",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
